The paper focuses on the analysis of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in relation to their ability to learn about objects. This topic is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), as CNNs are a popular tool for object recognition and classification tasks. The paper also discusses the invariance of CNNs to object-class variations, which is a topic that falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the CNN representations, which is a topic that falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
